WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:10.538 --> 00:00:14.420
PROFESSOR: I wanted to make a
few comments on the third

00:00:14.420 --> 00:00:17.530
problem set, which was
a funny puzzle.

00:00:17.530 --> 00:00:20.320
And it was intended to be
entertaining and get you

00:00:20.320 --> 00:00:23.320
thinking about things
related to symmetry

00:00:23.320 --> 00:00:25.250
in an amusing context.

00:00:25.250 --> 00:00:26.640
And there were two problems.

00:00:26.640 --> 00:00:32.030
The first problem had a platter
on which there were

00:00:32.030 --> 00:00:37.650
arranged cherries with either
two or three berries to a

00:00:37.650 --> 00:00:40.940
spray, and apples and pears.

00:00:40.940 --> 00:00:43.300
And they were either black or
white, which didn't make then

00:00:43.300 --> 00:00:45.130
particularly appetizing.

00:00:45.130 --> 00:00:51.140
But in any case, there were
three platters and the fruits

00:00:51.140 --> 00:00:53.020
marched around on the platter.

00:00:53.020 --> 00:00:57.760
And the puzzle was, what
would be the fourth

00:00:57.760 --> 00:01:00.280
platter in the sequence?

00:01:00.280 --> 00:01:04.090
This didn't involve symmetry
in any sense of the word.

00:01:04.090 --> 00:01:09.120
But yet, what was going on from
picture to picture was a

00:01:09.120 --> 00:01:13.410
mapping of the motifs from
one location to another.

00:01:13.410 --> 00:01:18.430
Not just rotation or translation
or anything nice

00:01:18.430 --> 00:01:21.870
in the crystallographic, but
still they were being moved

00:01:21.870 --> 00:01:24.010
from one location to another.

00:01:24.010 --> 00:01:27.300
And just about everybody
got the right

00:01:27.300 --> 00:01:31.420
answer just by deduction.

00:01:31.420 --> 00:01:34.430
But the reason I liked that
problem, and the reason I gave

00:01:34.430 --> 00:01:38.030
it to you, is that it introduced
another sort of

00:01:38.030 --> 00:01:40.660
transformation.

00:01:40.660 --> 00:01:44.000
One of the pairs of fruits not
only change locations, but

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:47.150
they switched from black to
white as you went from one

00:01:47.150 --> 00:01:49.260
position to the other.

00:01:49.260 --> 00:01:50.880
And that is another sort of

00:01:50.880 --> 00:01:53.250
transformation we can introduce.

00:01:53.250 --> 00:01:56.250
And this is something we could
call color symmetry.

00:01:56.250 --> 00:02:01.230
And I would observe that this
is something that you are

00:02:01.230 --> 00:02:06.830
already very familiar with in
patterns, in particular, in

00:02:06.830 --> 00:02:13.760
the pattern that is represented
by a checkerboard

00:02:13.760 --> 00:02:18.140
where you have black squares
and white squares.

00:02:18.140 --> 00:02:23.450
This location here is a bona
fide four-fold axis, as is

00:02:23.450 --> 00:02:26.010
this location here.

00:02:26.010 --> 00:02:30.670
But there other locations, such
as the corners of the

00:02:30.670 --> 00:02:35.180
black and white squares, where,
indeed, there is a 90

00:02:35.180 --> 00:02:38.390
degree rotation that takes this
square and transforms it

00:02:38.390 --> 00:02:39.360
into this square.

00:02:39.360 --> 00:02:41.680
But in doing that
transformation, you change it

00:02:41.680 --> 00:02:45.360
from a black one to a white one,
and then from a white one

00:02:45.360 --> 00:02:48.750
to a black one again,
back to a white one.

00:02:48.750 --> 00:02:52.962
And that is a color symmetry.

00:02:52.962 --> 00:02:55.880
You could make it red and green
if you like to be a

00:02:55.880 --> 00:02:57.280
little more attractive.

00:02:57.280 --> 00:03:01.190
Similarly, there are mirror
lines like this that are true

00:03:01.190 --> 00:03:02.240
mirror lines.

00:03:02.240 --> 00:03:04.030
The pattern is left invariant.

00:03:04.030 --> 00:03:07.140
There's another locus such as
this one here where when you

00:03:07.140 --> 00:03:11.050
reflect you go from a black one
to white one and then back

00:03:11.050 --> 00:03:14.600
to a black one when you do
the operation twice.

00:03:14.600 --> 00:03:17.230
So there are black-white mirror
planes as well as

00:03:17.230 --> 00:03:18.830
regular mirror planes.

00:03:18.830 --> 00:03:22.160
There are two-fold axes but all
of the two-fold axes are

00:03:22.160 --> 00:03:26.390
black-white axes, white to
black, black back to white.

00:03:26.390 --> 00:03:30.070
So that's a new sort of
transformation that we can

00:03:30.070 --> 00:03:32.540
develop if we wanted to,
switching the color.

00:03:35.370 --> 00:03:37.910
Does this is have any utility
in the physical sciences?

00:03:37.910 --> 00:03:40.510
Be nice for wallpaper designers,
but does it have

00:03:40.510 --> 00:03:42.360
utility in physical sciences?

00:03:42.360 --> 00:03:43.990
And the answer is yes.

00:03:43.990 --> 00:03:47.760
Because what is going on here
is that there is a binary

00:03:47.760 --> 00:03:50.500
character assigned to
each of the motifs.

00:03:50.500 --> 00:03:52.990
So any time the atom or
whatever you have, the

00:03:52.990 --> 00:03:57.240
molecule, has some sort of
binary characteristic that it

00:03:57.240 --> 00:04:00.840
can exist in two distinct
states, the arrangement of

00:04:00.840 --> 00:04:05.080
that sort of motif requires
a black-white symmetry.

00:04:05.080 --> 00:04:09.080
And one example in crystals
that requires this sort of

00:04:09.080 --> 00:04:12.610
symmetry is the case of
a magnetic structure--

00:04:12.610 --> 00:04:15.480
and I think I mentioned this
last time-- where the magnetic

00:04:15.480 --> 00:04:17.760
moment can either point
up or down.

00:04:17.760 --> 00:04:20.500
Well, saying that you have an
atom with spin up and an atom

00:04:20.500 --> 00:04:23.470
with spin down is the same thing
as saying, in terms of

00:04:23.470 --> 00:04:27.140
transformations, having a black
atom or a white atom.

00:04:27.140 --> 00:04:33.270
It's a binary character that
switches from atom to atom.

00:04:33.270 --> 00:04:36.314
Could you have three
color symmetries?

00:04:36.314 --> 00:04:36.746
Yeah.

00:04:36.746 --> 00:04:37.830
You can.

00:04:37.830 --> 00:04:44.020
There is a Dutch artist named
Maurits Escher who spent much

00:04:44.020 --> 00:04:48.280
of his, career deducing
patterns, and did this in a

00:04:48.280 --> 00:04:50.080
purely intuitive way.

00:04:50.080 --> 00:04:52.100
I mean you look at these
patterns and say, wow, that

00:04:52.100 --> 00:04:54.470
guy is some crystallographer.

00:04:54.470 --> 00:04:58.310
But I heard him, while he was
still alive, speak twice.

00:04:58.310 --> 00:05:01.700
And he describes it in
metaphysical terms.

00:05:01.700 --> 00:05:06.330
This is the twoness merging with
the fourness, and just

00:05:06.330 --> 00:05:08.580
completely intuitive.

00:05:08.580 --> 00:05:09.790
But his patterns are gorgeous.

00:05:09.790 --> 00:05:12.650
And he has a number of very nice
ones that are three-color

00:05:12.650 --> 00:05:13.790
symmetries.

00:05:13.790 --> 00:05:16.410
And maybe later on in the
term, I'll bring in a

00:05:16.410 --> 00:05:18.520
projector and show you examples
of some of these.

00:05:18.520 --> 00:05:19.770
They're very entertaining.

00:05:22.280 --> 00:05:22.520
All right.

00:05:22.520 --> 00:05:25.420
So the purpose of that first
puzzle was to introduce you to

00:05:25.420 --> 00:05:26.670
black-white symmetries.

00:05:28.990 --> 00:05:32.390
Then the second puzzle on the
sheet was a pretty dumb thing.

00:05:32.390 --> 00:05:36.310
There was a stack of blocks
and you said how many--

00:05:36.310 --> 00:05:40.070
I asked how many blocks are
there in the stack?

00:05:40.070 --> 00:05:42.250
And you could count them
up, 1, 2, 3, 4.

00:05:42.250 --> 00:05:44.790
And If you did it right,
you came out with 32.

00:05:44.790 --> 00:05:46.570
So that was pretty dumb.

00:05:46.570 --> 00:05:51.090
Well, this was intended as an
example of how one can use

00:05:51.090 --> 00:05:56.610
symmetry in the solution
of a physical problem.

00:05:56.610 --> 00:05:59.140
Let's suppose that you were a
cowboy and you had to go out

00:05:59.140 --> 00:06:02.230
and buy horseshoes for
a herd of horses.

00:06:02.230 --> 00:06:04.660
Would you count the
number of feet?

00:06:04.660 --> 00:06:04.960
No.

00:06:04.960 --> 00:06:08.924
You'd count the number of horses
and multiply by four.

00:06:08.924 --> 00:06:09.750
OK.

00:06:09.750 --> 00:06:12.061
So there you'd be
using symmetry.

00:06:12.061 --> 00:06:15.826
Now The point of this
problem really was--

00:06:15.826 --> 00:06:17.535
You could have had this one.

00:06:17.535 --> 00:06:20.600
We have just the exact
number seats.

00:06:20.600 --> 00:06:27.092
The point of this problem was
that you have to, in assigning

00:06:27.092 --> 00:06:31.140
a symmetry to a system,
usually make physical

00:06:31.140 --> 00:06:32.290
assumptions.

00:06:32.290 --> 00:06:35.470
When you do a derivation, as
we've been doing for the last

00:06:35.470 --> 00:06:38.490
several days, we say this is a
four-fold access, and there's

00:06:38.490 --> 00:06:40.410
no ambiguity whatsoever.

00:06:40.410 --> 00:06:43.110
Because it's my ball game, and
I want it to be a four-fold

00:06:43.110 --> 00:06:44.720
axis,

00:06:44.720 --> 00:06:47.480
But when you're given a pattern
or given a crystal and

00:06:47.480 --> 00:06:50.500
you have to assign a symmetry
to that crystal, you

00:06:50.500 --> 00:06:53.840
invariably have to
make assumptions.

00:06:53.840 --> 00:06:56.410
The person buying the
horseshoes, for example, has

00:06:56.410 --> 00:07:00.390
to assume that five- and
six-legged horses are pretty

00:07:00.390 --> 00:07:07.350
rare articles and that a horse
with only three or two legs is

00:07:07.350 --> 00:07:09.905
going to be of little utility
to the rancher.

00:07:09.905 --> 00:07:12.680
It Would probably have a limited
existence at the

00:07:12.680 --> 00:07:13.960
ranchers expense.

00:07:13.960 --> 00:07:19.240
So you're assuming that all
horse have four legs.

00:07:19.240 --> 00:07:23.110
In looking at a crystal, though,
things are not that

00:07:23.110 --> 00:07:24.460
easy to decide.

00:07:24.460 --> 00:07:28.140
And let me give you a few really
practical examples.

00:07:28.140 --> 00:07:31.490
A lot of mineral crystals grow
in fissures in the rock.

00:07:31.490 --> 00:07:34.970
And let's suppose we've got a
crack, and bubbling through

00:07:34.970 --> 00:07:39.050
this crack is a solution
that contains silica.

00:07:39.050 --> 00:07:41.690
And as the solution cools
off, it will deposit

00:07:41.690 --> 00:07:43.140
a crystal of quartz.

00:07:43.140 --> 00:07:47.010
And this crystal of quartz would
probably grow looking

00:07:47.010 --> 00:07:49.370
something like this.

00:07:49.370 --> 00:07:51.440
And you would knock the crystal
out of the rock.

00:07:51.440 --> 00:07:54.075
And you would say, what is the
symmetry of this crystal?

00:07:56.890 --> 00:07:59.890
It doesn't appear to be anything
hexagonal about it.

00:08:02.420 --> 00:08:06.990
But what's happened is this
crystal if it had developed in

00:08:06.990 --> 00:08:11.660
a uniform environment would have
had a hexagonal shape.

00:08:11.660 --> 00:08:15.040
But because the nutrients are
flowing in from one direction,

00:08:15.040 --> 00:08:17.990
it tends to elongate
in that direction.

00:08:17.990 --> 00:08:22.640
So how could you assign the
symmetry to that crystal that

00:08:22.640 --> 00:08:24.840
you dug out of the rock?

00:08:24.840 --> 00:08:28.330
Unfortunately, crystals do not
come with a legend on the

00:08:28.330 --> 00:08:37.409
bottom that says quartz SIO2
space group P3 subscript 121,

00:08:37.409 --> 00:08:38.960
made in USA.

00:08:38.960 --> 00:08:42.860
You have to yourself assign
the symmetry.

00:08:42.860 --> 00:08:45.500
And what you would do is you
would look at this face and

00:08:45.500 --> 00:08:48.050
this face and you say, gee,
these angles, when I measure

00:08:48.050 --> 00:08:51.720
them, all turn out to
be 120 degrees.

00:08:51.720 --> 00:08:54.610
This face has a luster on
it that looks like the

00:08:54.610 --> 00:08:56.190
luster on this face.

00:08:56.190 --> 00:08:59.360
This face has little edge pits
on it, and they point in the

00:08:59.360 --> 00:09:02.820
same way as the edge
pits on this face.

00:09:02.820 --> 00:09:06.190
I can measure the electrical
conductivity and find that it

00:09:06.190 --> 00:09:09.830
varies in a fashion consistent
with a hexagonal crystal.

00:09:09.830 --> 00:09:13.390
And you would do any physical
test that you decided you

00:09:13.390 --> 00:09:14.430
would need to make.

00:09:14.430 --> 00:09:17.650
And then when you were all done,
you would say everything

00:09:17.650 --> 00:09:20.810
that I can measure about this
crystal other than it's shape

00:09:20.810 --> 00:09:28.060
is invariant to a 120
degree rotation.

00:09:28.060 --> 00:09:34.100
Quartz has a hexagonal shape
very often, but actually only

00:09:34.100 --> 00:09:38.120
this face, this face, and this
face are symmetrically

00:09:38.120 --> 00:09:38.760
equivalent.

00:09:38.760 --> 00:09:41.350
And there's only a three-fold
axis in there.

00:09:41.350 --> 00:09:44.550
And if you look very carefully
at this crystal, you could see

00:09:44.550 --> 00:09:46.130
some difference there, too.

00:09:46.130 --> 00:09:50.085
The neighboring faces very often
have striations, very

00:09:50.085 --> 00:09:53.210
faint striations on one face,
no striations on the

00:09:53.210 --> 00:09:54.890
neighboring face.

00:09:54.890 --> 00:09:56.540
So you find out all that can.

00:09:56.540 --> 00:09:59.550
You have to make some
assumptions, and then on that

00:09:59.550 --> 00:10:02.860
basis decide the symmetry.

00:10:02.860 --> 00:10:03.920
Let me give you another
example.

00:10:03.920 --> 00:10:04.960
This is a real one.

00:10:04.960 --> 00:10:08.210
And one of the things that
it's fun to do is to grow

00:10:08.210 --> 00:10:09.780
crystals from solution.

00:10:09.780 --> 00:10:13.040
The Science Museum has little
kits that you can buy that

00:10:13.040 --> 00:10:16.150
have some powder that you could
heat up in water and

00:10:16.150 --> 00:10:20.420
then put it in a beaker and put
a string in there, maybe

00:10:20.420 --> 00:10:23.480
with a little crumb of the
stuff that you dissolved.

00:10:23.480 --> 00:10:26.340
And one of the crystals
that is nice for

00:10:26.340 --> 00:10:30.410
this purpose is alum.

00:10:30.410 --> 00:10:31.790
It's a cubic crystal.

00:10:31.790 --> 00:10:36.810
And if you let the stuff set
there, it will form a nice,

00:10:36.810 --> 00:10:39.063
lovely equiaxed cubed.

00:10:39.063 --> 00:10:43.190
Science Museum usually puts a
pinch of another salt in there

00:10:43.190 --> 00:10:46.330
so the crystal is not only
pretty and shiny, it's purple

00:10:46.330 --> 00:10:48.725
or it's the orange.

00:10:48.725 --> 00:10:52.830
Now, unless you attach this
little seed crystal carefully,

00:10:52.830 --> 00:10:56.230
there would be a good chance
that it would fall off and

00:10:56.230 --> 00:10:57.850
land on the bottom
of the beaker.

00:10:57.850 --> 00:11:01.180
When that happened, your crystal
would not have the

00:11:01.180 --> 00:11:03.670
shape of a cube.

00:11:03.670 --> 00:11:08.060
It would have a shape in which
these two top edges had length

00:11:08.060 --> 00:11:13.970
L and these faces on the side
were exactly half that length.

00:11:13.970 --> 00:11:16.560
And what's happening is that
this crystal is growing in an

00:11:16.560 --> 00:11:18.335
unconstrained environment.

00:11:18.335 --> 00:11:21.640
The nutrient is coming on and
crystallizing from all

00:11:21.640 --> 00:11:22.820
directions.

00:11:22.820 --> 00:11:27.830
In this case, nutrient can't
get in from the directions

00:11:27.830 --> 00:11:29.270
that are below the crystal.

00:11:29.270 --> 00:11:32.780
So the growth in that direction
is eliminated, and

00:11:32.780 --> 00:11:35.100
this height is exactly
half that at

00:11:35.100 --> 00:11:37.880
the edge of the crystal.

00:11:37.880 --> 00:11:41.480
So that's sort of a very
specialized case of a crystal

00:11:41.480 --> 00:11:43.225
growing in a constrained
environment.

00:11:47.160 --> 00:11:50.110
I'm digressing now, but let me
make a few more remarks.

00:11:50.110 --> 00:11:52.485
The shape that a crystal has--

00:11:55.930 --> 00:11:59.170
and the shape is in
crystallography designated by

00:11:59.170 --> 00:12:00.460
a special term.

00:12:00.460 --> 00:12:01.710
It's called habit.

00:12:06.450 --> 00:12:10.960
Crystals that undergo plastic
deformation never die, they

00:12:10.960 --> 00:12:12.280
just develop bad habits.

00:12:15.020 --> 00:12:15.590
Oh, come on.

00:12:15.590 --> 00:12:18.070
This is a tough crowd.

00:12:18.070 --> 00:12:19.510
I thought that was
pretty funny.

00:12:19.510 --> 00:12:20.810
Anyway.

00:12:20.810 --> 00:12:25.420
The habit that a crystal has
can depend very much on

00:12:25.420 --> 00:12:29.730
impurities in the solution or
melt from which it grows.

00:12:29.730 --> 00:12:33.340
And let me suppose I start with
a little crystal that

00:12:33.340 --> 00:12:35.650
looks like this.

00:12:35.650 --> 00:12:39.640
And there are two different
kinds of faces on there.

00:12:39.640 --> 00:12:42.540
And let's suppose one of them
grows rapidly and one of them

00:12:42.540 --> 00:12:44.060
grows slowly.

00:12:44.060 --> 00:12:48.050
Which face do you think would
be the one that eventually

00:12:48.050 --> 00:12:51.000
forms the boundaries to
the crystal volume?

00:12:51.000 --> 00:12:54.714
The fast-growing face or
the slow-growing face?

00:12:54.714 --> 00:12:55.670
AUDIENCE: Fast-growing face.

00:12:55.670 --> 00:12:58.640
PROFESSOR: Fast, slow are
both possibilities.

00:12:58.640 --> 00:13:00.320
Let's do a time lapse
experiment.

00:13:00.320 --> 00:13:02.840
Let's suppose that this is
the fast-growing face.

00:13:02.840 --> 00:13:06.070
And, after a certain amount of
time these faces would have

00:13:06.070 --> 00:13:09.260
all advanced to this location.

00:13:09.260 --> 00:13:10.820
And this is the slow-growing
face.

00:13:10.820 --> 00:13:14.210
And after the same amount of
time, it will have advanced to

00:13:14.210 --> 00:13:16.550
this location.

00:13:16.550 --> 00:13:18.650
After the next time increment,
this one would

00:13:18.650 --> 00:13:20.100
have grown up to here.

00:13:20.100 --> 00:13:22.270
This would only have
grown that far.

00:13:22.270 --> 00:13:25.620
And you could see the only thing
that's gonna be left is

00:13:25.620 --> 00:13:27.350
the slow-growing face.

00:13:27.350 --> 00:13:29.480
So it's sort of counter
intuitive.

00:13:29.480 --> 00:13:32.740
The faces that survive to bound
the crystal as rational

00:13:32.740 --> 00:13:35.430
planes are the slow-growing
faces, not the

00:13:35.430 --> 00:13:36.680
rapidly growing faces.

00:13:39.050 --> 00:13:42.670
This is of great use to the
people who want to control

00:13:42.670 --> 00:13:45.330
crystal shape.

00:13:45.330 --> 00:13:51.020
And this is very often in very
every day, ordinary contexts.

00:13:51.020 --> 00:13:53.890
The people who grow table salt,
for example, want to

00:13:53.890 --> 00:13:57.360
grow a crystal that has nice
pointy edges so when it comes

00:13:57.360 --> 00:13:59.880
down on your tomato, it
doesn't bounce off.

00:13:59.880 --> 00:14:02.110
It sticks to it.

00:14:02.110 --> 00:14:03.930
So the shape of table
salt makes a

00:14:03.930 --> 00:14:06.260
difference in how it behaves.

00:14:06.260 --> 00:14:09.250
And the way you change the shape
is to find something

00:14:09.250 --> 00:14:12.760
that will be absorbed
preferentially on one set of

00:14:12.760 --> 00:14:17.060
faces that you would like to
have be the faces that appear

00:14:17.060 --> 00:14:18.470
on the crystal.

00:14:18.470 --> 00:14:22.980
And that will do the
job for you.

00:14:22.980 --> 00:14:27.070
I'll close with just one final
example of this in real, every

00:14:27.070 --> 00:14:29.230
day industry or technology.

00:14:29.230 --> 00:14:35.790
I once had a phone call from a
company that made salt for

00:14:35.790 --> 00:14:38.240
sprinkling on roads in the
winter time, particularly

00:14:38.240 --> 00:14:41.830
around New England when the
roads tend to ice up.

00:14:41.830 --> 00:14:46.070
And in an earlier era it, was
politically correct to use

00:14:46.070 --> 00:14:47.760
sodium chloride.

00:14:47.760 --> 00:14:51.760
But you wanted the sodium
chloride, if you could, to

00:14:51.760 --> 00:14:55.270
have an acicular, a needle-like,
shape to improve

00:14:55.270 --> 00:14:57.680
its flow properties so you
didn't waste a lot when you

00:14:57.680 --> 00:15:00.120
shook it out of the
back of the truck.

00:15:00.120 --> 00:15:04.680
And the material that they use
for that-- you think rock salt

00:15:04.680 --> 00:15:06.450
in the environment is bad--

00:15:06.450 --> 00:15:11.580
they used a cyanide compound to
modify the growth habit and

00:15:11.580 --> 00:15:13.430
make it needle-like.

00:15:13.430 --> 00:15:15.970
And they wanted to get away
from that before they were

00:15:15.970 --> 00:15:22.330
really dragged into some sort
of trial by the EPA.

00:15:22.330 --> 00:15:27.420
And did I know of something that
could change the shape of

00:15:27.420 --> 00:15:29.025
the salt crystals for them?

00:15:29.025 --> 00:15:30.720
And the answer to that
question was quite

00:15:30.720 --> 00:15:31.560
straightforward.

00:15:31.560 --> 00:15:32.450
No.

00:15:32.450 --> 00:15:34.100
That was the end of
the conversation.

00:15:34.100 --> 00:15:36.760
But it was an interesting
example of how surface

00:15:36.760 --> 00:15:39.090
chemistry can change
crystal shape.

00:15:43.790 --> 00:15:44.260
OK.

00:15:44.260 --> 00:15:46.480
So all that long-winded
explanation was a

00:15:46.480 --> 00:15:49.130
justification of the
meaning of those

00:15:49.130 --> 00:15:51.490
two final two puzzles.

00:15:51.490 --> 00:15:54.010
And the final thing I have to
